      <scopecontent id="aspace_52f8f3b1c260d5505e0fd9838d5bef78">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection contains various papers (1681-1869) relating to several New Hampshire and Maine Towns. Included is a small amount of correspondence, including one letter signed by the Margquis de Lafayette (1831). Other papers include the original proprietor's grant to Bretton Woods, New Hampshire, deeds and tax receipts for land in the New Hamphire towns of Bretton Woods, Dummer, and Portsmouth, mostly relating to the Haven family, several documents signed by New Hampshire Governor, John Wentworth, and a variety of personal papers of the Rollins and Hooker families of Portsmouth.</p>
         <p>This collection was donated by Anna and Marion Tompson to Yale University in 1946.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
